sp.p:
If I  give  you the copy of the Cities countenance, 
 I will   not flatter the face, as painters do; 
but show  all  the wrinkles of it.

Nor  ever  shalt: why the great Turke is a very little fellow; 
 I  have  seen a scurvy little bad paltry Christian, has 
 been   taken for the greatest Turke there.
